# Polymarket API Configuration Example
# Copy this file to .env.polymarket and fill in your credentials

# ==============================================================================
# WALLET CREDENTIALS (Required)
# ==============================================================================

# Your Ethereum private key (with or without 0x prefix)
# ⚠️ CRITICAL: Keep this secret! Never commit to git!
# Generate via: MetaMask, Phantom, or any Ethereum wallet
POLYMARKET_PRIVATE_KEY=your_private_key_here

# Your wallet address (derived automatically if not provided)
# Example: 0x1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef12345678
POLYMARKET_WALLET_ADDRESS=your_wallet_address_here

# Chain ID (137 = Polygon mainnet)
# Note: Polymarket only operates on Polygon mainnet (no testnet available)
POLYMARKET_CHAIN_ID=137

# ==============================================================================
# API ENDPOINTS (Optional - defaults provided)
# ==============================================================================

# Gamma API (market data - read-only)
POLYMARKET_GAMMA_URL=https://gamma-api.polymarket.com

# CLOB API (trading - requires authentication)
POLYMARKET_CLOB_URL=https://clob.polymarket.com

# ==============================================================================
# RATE LIMITING (Optional)
# ==============================================================================

# Maximum API calls per minute
POLYMARKET_RATE_LIMIT_CALLS=100

# Rate limit period in seconds
POLYMARKET_RATE_LIMIT_PERIOD=60

# ==============================================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ==============================================================================

# 1. NO TESTNET: Polymarket has no demo/testnet environment
#    - All trades use real USDC on Polygon mainnet
#    - Start with small amounts for testing
#    - You are responsible for all trades executed

# 2. WALLET FUNDING:
#    - You need USDC on Polygon for trading
#    - You need small amount of MATIC for gas fees
#    - Bridge from Ethereum or buy directly on Polygon

# 3. SECURITY:
#    - Never commit .env.polymarket to git
#    - Keep your private key secure
#    - You control the funds (non-custodial)
#    - Lost private key = lost funds

# 4. API CREDENTIALS:
#    - API key/secret obtained automatically via EIP-712 signing
#    - First call to trading tools will authenticate
#    - Credentials cached for session

# ==============================================================================
# SETUP CHECKLIST
# ==============================================================================

# [ ] 1. Create Ethereum wallet (MetaMask, Phantom, etc.)
# [ ] 2. Export private key from wallet
# [ ] 3. Copy this file to .env.polymarket
# [ ] 4. Add POLYMARKET_PRIVATE_KEY to .env.polymarket
# [ ] 5. Fund wallet with USDC on Polygon (for trading)
# [ ] 6. Fund wallet with MATIC (for gas fees - ~$1 worth)
# [ ] 7. Test with small amounts first
# [ ] 8. Verify .env.polymarket is in .gitignore

# ==============================================================================
# GETTING STARTED
# ==============================================================================

# 1. Fund your wallet:
#    - Bridge USDC to Polygon: https://wallet.polygon.technology/
#    - Or buy USDC directly on Polygon via exchanges
#    - Get MATIC for gas: Polygon faucets or exchanges

# 2. Test the connection:
#    - Run: python -c "from src.polymarket.gamma_client import GammaClient; import asyncio; asyncio.run(GammaClient.from_env().search_markets(limit=1))"

# 3. Authenticate:
#    - First trading operation will prompt for EIP-712 signature
#    - API credentials obtained automatically
#    - No manual API key generation needed

# ==============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ==============================================================================

# Error: "Invalid private key"
#   - Ensure private key is correct (with or without 0x prefix)
#   - Check if key is from correct wallet

# Error: "Insufficient balance"
#   - Check USDC balance on Polygon
#   - Verify you're on Polygon mainnet (chain ID 137)

# Error: "Gas estimation failed"
#   - Ensure you have MATIC for gas fees
#   - Check if wallet is on Polygon network

# Error: "Authentication failed"
#   - Verify private key is correct
#   - Check network connectivity
#   - Try again (authentication is automatic)

